body_html:
There are two test issues.
First with the function_test:
https://source.cloud.google.com/results/invocations/6b22c584-f73d-4c1b-b939-1c68fce02e6e/targets/%2F%2Ftensorflow%2Fpython:function_test?page=log

2nd, api_compatibility_test:
https://source.cloud.google.com/results/invocations/6b22c584-f73d-4c1b-b939-1c68fce02e6e/targets/%2F%2Ftensorflow%2Ftools%2Fapi%2Ftests:api_compatibility_test?page=log

    $ bazel build tensorflow/tools/api/tests:api_compatibility_test
    $ bazel-bin/tensorflow/tools/api/tests/api_compatibility_test \
          --update_goldens True

You will need an API approval to make changes to the public TensorFlow API. This
includes additions to the API.

These instructions should be followed on a linux machine with python 2.
